SIMPLE: sisterhood
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sisterhood
<hw>Sis"ter*hood</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Sister</ets> + <ets>hood</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
state or relation of being a sister; the office or duty of a
sister.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She . . . abhorr'd⟦br⟧
Her proper blood, and left to do the part⟦br⟧
Of <qex>sisterhood</qex>, to do that of a wife.</q>
<rj><qau>Daniel.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A society of sisters; a society of women united in
one faith or order; sisters, collectively.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A
<xex>sisterhood</xex> of holy nuns.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The fair young flowers . . . a beauteous
<qex>sisterhood</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Bryant.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sistering</ent>⟦br⟧
